,Recommended,303800,14857987,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,Epicje,"This game is technically solid. There's good music, there's a nice atmosphere, the encounters are cool and the interaction is nearly well excecuted. It's a very well thought out board game, with minor flaws and weird 'fast travel' systems that just robs you of your money.With nearly well, I mean that the AI is A) dumb as hell, B) cheats.As for the dumbness - the AI tends to just spend all their development cards for 1 fight, while s/he should only need 1. Then there's the endless 'fast travelling' that they're doing and making things harder for themselves.Then there's the fact that they simply refuse to complete their main quest. Dandelion for example, had 6 purple proof items and kept spending gold on 1 more every time he could, while avoiding the main quest area.This didn't happen once or twice, this happens nearly every game I'm playing.As for the cheating, I'm convinced that they don't cheat with the dice rolls, but there are cards like Dijkstra's thugs, that makes you have to cash in 2 investigation tokens. Or, if they lose a fight, to hand over 1 or 2 tokens. The AI doesn't have to do this for some unexplained reason. I've also seen instances where they become 'delayed' and still perform 2 actions, while not having a good fortune card to ignore the delay.All in all, it's not a masterpiece, but deffinatly worth spending 1 hour per day for a round of fun and the price tag isn't too bad either.Here's to hoping that the patch removes these weird AI issues.****************I'm going to ADD to this review, rather than edit it with strikethrough.A new patch came out recently and fixed every single bit of gripes I had with this game. Now it's a challenge, the AI doesn't cheat with Dijkstra's Thugs, they don't derp around for an eternity and makes this game a HUGE challenge.Thanks CDRP, for listening to your customers!"
