,Recommended,303800,14641234,"Posted: 24 February, 2015",all,Mr. Awesome,"Not a bad game at all, though I feel it lacks a little polish and content.Pros:It's fun. It's challenging.And in all, a great game if you're into boardgames.Multiplayer both online and as hotseat.Cons:Needs a proper tutorial - even though there are short videos to explain the basics, it doesn't cover everything, which eventually will send you to the rules section for tedious reading.And even those rules are taken directly from the hardcopy boardgame, with instructions to place your playing piece on the side, and stuff like that.You'll pick it up as you play, but a proper tutorial would have been better.Needs more cards, especially for battle encounters.Playing a 4 player game with a 5 quest goal, with have you battling the same few handfuls of monsters over and over.And quests are pretty much all the same - strip the description and you're down to 'collect X tokens of type Y' and go to place Z.Game mechanics are a bit shoddy.You can pretty much spend the first ten turns drawing development cards to OP your character.And often rewards  are penalties to the leading player, which kinda blows if you pick a reward that actually penalizes you.Character balance is off, with Geralt with a severe lead on the others, by having 2 more dice to roll for combat encounters.Yeah, the others have other advantages, but bashing monsters is a good way to rack up victory points, which makes a free skill for Triss to run away without penalty kinda bleak and useless in comparison.In a long game, I don't see how you can lose with Geralt.Conclusion:It's decent enough to recommend, but wouldn't say it's worth the full asking price of 10€.Picked it up on a deal for 6€, which I think is a more appropriate pricerange, all considered.You will have a good few hours of fun with it, but I'm imagining it gets kind of pointless once you've played all the characters and handful of times, simply because the character balance is totally off, the game mechanics have obvious exploits and are somewhat poorly designed, and it lacks diversity and content for longer games.But that's just my opinion. I'm a boardgame geek, and I have been designing games since I was a 10 year old kid back in the 80's, so I spot the flaws immediately.You could end up having a fantastic time with this game, regardless of what I think."
