76561197990527641,Not Recommended,303800,13118022,"Posted: 27 November, 2014",all,Outlier Joe,"As far as a digital implementation of a board game, this is fairly good. It's a nice PC interface. Everything works fairly well. (The dice are a little funky, but eh... whatever).I love the Witcher series. I was excited when this game was announced. I was excited to see this game hit the store.If you you love The Witcher Adventure Game, and want a digital implementation, then stop reading and just buy it.If you haven't played The Witcher Adventure Game, let me stop you right there and say ""Don't"". Go buy Merchants of Venus, Xia: Legend of a Drift System, Steam, Merchants & Marauders, Istanbul, or even Firefly: The Game. Those are all vastly superior Pick-Up and Deliver games - which is all this is. An unnessessarily complicated, frustrating, painful, lengthy Pick-Up and Deliver game.It's a mean game. And I don't mean that in the way that Diplomacy or even Munchkin is a ""mean game"". Or even how ""Ghost Stories is brutally difficult"". I mean this game stabs you in the liver, and then deducts points from you because you're bleeding like a wimp.The designer is a wonderful designer. He also owns the game publisher ""Portal Games"". Go check out all of his other games (Robinson Crusoe, Imperial Settlers, 51st State, The New Era, Pret-a-Porter). This doesn't even measure up to the worst game I've played from Fantasy Flight.The interaction between players is awful. It's mostly a solitare experience. Which doesn't help when the game points how you don't have any friends.The turns are very repetative. Especially when the game finally gets you into the fetal position, and all it leaves you to do is to rock back and forth as you bleed from your severed ankles.Ever played Bunco? Where you just roll the dice, hoping to roll three of a kind? No agency. No decision making. Just luck of the RNG. This game wants you to roll a 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, or 10 of a kind with 3-4 dice - and that's not really an exaggeration.When when you fail, because - well - math, you take damage.Nothing good really happens to you. And when it does, like finally completing one of your quests, you STILL get punished. For a good ol' fashioned ""Good job. ♥♥♥♥ you."" - like mom use to say.The monsters seem incredibly out of balance. Rolling the dice usually seems like a wasted effort. There ARE things you HAVE to get in order to over come the dice, but those dont' seem well balanced either.This is easily one of the worst board game experiences I've had in the last few years.The only value this game has had for me is that I only spent $8 on this before foolishly spending $60 at my local game store. And for that, I'll look very favorably at it.10/10."
