76561198050918249,Recommended,303800,18343381,"Posted: 5 October, 2015",all,Bloodyalice,"I actually haven't played The Witcher series yet but I thought the board game looked cool so I gave it a try and glad I did.   You do not have to have any type of knowledge about the series to do well in this game.  There is basically the same learning curve regardless.  You will spend the first couple of games making some mistakes (unless you do your homework) but it's really that as difficult as it looks at first glace.  Don't give up within the first 15 mins, it will all come together after a couple games.I haven't played against random online or AI, so I cannot comment on that, however; if you have people to play with then it goes very smooth for the most part.  I disconnected once, which can be frustrating because there is no save and you lose your progress in the game.Overall, a really fun game game to play with your friends.  Animation looks great, gameplay feels like an actual boardgame, would love to see some more games like this.Keep in mind this game does generally take at least a couple hours to play per round and can take longer."
