,Recommended,303800,24227775,"Posted: 10 July, 2016",all,Bailey,"If you're a fan of The WItcher series, or if you're looking for a turn based 'card game'. then I would recommend The Witcher Adventure Game. As stated in previous reviews, the tutorial needs work, as it does tend to gloss over some of the game mechanics. The tutorials do cover quite a few important features though, so it isn't completely redundent.If you're looking at this title hoping that it would be similar to Gwent, it isn't. It's far more involved than Gwent, and requires far more time to pick up and to play through.For it's price, it's worth picking up, and when future updates are released (hopefully expanding the tutorial and adding a few more playable characters) it should give you plenty of reasons to sink a fair amount of time into this game.TL;DR:It's not Gwent. It's a board game that most users who enjoyed The Witcher would enjoy. It takes a while to pick up and play, but it's worth it."
